data.description: Welcome to this exquisite five-bedroom, three and a half bathroom home nestled on a sprawling 20-acre parcel of land, perfectly positioned adjacent to BLM territory, just a stone's throw away from the charming town of Gunnison. This remarkable property offers an abundance of space and a myriad of amenities that are sure to capture your heart.  As you step inside, you'll be greeted by a spacious living room that basks in natural light, thanks to the large bay window that offers picturesque views of the surrounding landscape. The cozy ambiance is further enhanced by a pellet stove, perfect for those chilly Colorado evenings.  The heart of this home is the remodeled kitchen, showcasing custom cabinets, a gas range, and a double oven that will surely delight the chef in your family. The elegant wainscoting adorns the adjacent eat-in breakfast nook, creating a warm and inviting atmosphere.  On the main floor, you'll find the primary bedroom, complete with an en-suite bathroom, providing a tranquil retreat for homeowners. Two additional bedrooms and a full bathroom are conveniently located nearby.  Venturing to the second story, you'll discover two more generously sized bedrooms and another full bathroom, providing plenty of space for family and guests.  For those who love to entertain, the secondary dining room, just off the kitchen, features a custom-built china cabinet, adding a touch of sophistication to your gatherings. Through elegant French doors, you'll find a cozy den with a wood-burning fireplace, creating the perfect spot to unwind after a long day.  A sunroom located off the back living room is a sun-filled oasis, complete with a hot tub, where you can relax and soak in the serenity of your surroundings. This well-cared-for home is adorned with custom features throughout, ensuring both comfort and style.  The exterior of the property is equally impressive, featuring a 2,400 square foot heated shop with its own separate electric meter. Equipped with propane radiant heaters, this space is ideal for woodworking or heated storage for your boats, RVs, or work vehicles. The oversized garage door and custom-built loading dock add to its functionality. Additionally, there's a three-car garage, perfect for housing additional vehicles, tractors, or providing covered storage.  One of the most remarkable features of this property is its 20 acres of private land, bordering public land on two sides, making it a paradise for outdoor enthusiasts. With no HOA restrictions and only two adjoining neighbors, you'll enjoy the utmost privacy. The adjacent Signal Peak Trail System is visible from the property, and a two-track road connects you to this outdoor playground.  While you'll relish the remote living experience, the convenience of being just five minutes from downtown Gunnison ensures that you have access to all the amenities and services you need. Don't miss the opportunity to make this extraordinary property your own—call today for a private showing and discover the endless possibilities that await you in this exceptional home.
